HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1605
By Travis
A RESOLUTION to commend Carolyn Cates for her honorable
and astute service to the Sequatchie County
Election Commission.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should specially
recognize those estimable public servants who have dedicated themselves to improving the
quality of life for their fellow citizens; and
WHEREAS, Carolyn Cates is one such estimable person, who has devoted more than
four decades of service to the Sequatchie County Election Commission; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Cates began her career with the Sequatchie County Election
Commission in 1982 as a typist under administrator Helen Barker and was soon asked to
remain to assist with early voting operations; and
WHEREAS, over the course of her distinguished tenure, she has served under four
administrators of elections, including Helen Barker, Donald Britt, Linda Pittman, and current
administrator Jerrie Holland; and
WHEREAS, demonstrating both capability and commitment, Ms. Cates served as interim
Administrator of Elections, providing steady leadership and continuity during a period of
transition; and
WHEREAS, throughout her forty-four years of service, Carolyn Cates has contributed to
the efficient administration of elections in Sequatchie County, helping to ensure the integrity,
accuracy, and accessibility of the electoral process for all citizens; and
WHEREAS, known for her dedication, reliability, and institutional knowledge, Ms. Cates
has earned the respect and appreciation of her colleagues and the community she serves; and
WHEREAS, throughout her career, Carolyn Cates has exemplified the highest standards
of professionalism, ability, and integrity, reflecting great credit upon herself and the Sequatchie
County Election Commission; and
HJR1605
018558
- 1 -

WHEREAS, Ms. Cates is wholly committed to the noble precepts of public service that
have earned Tennessee recognition as the Volunteer State, and she should be specially
recognized; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we hereby commend Carolyn Cates for her honorable and astute service
to the Sequatchie County Election Commission, commend her ongoing commitment to public
service, and thank her for a difficult job well done.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
